title: gDRtestData
text: Since gDR computational suite drug response data experiment, synthetic dataset also needed testing exploration. basis package two functions generate synthetic sets cell lines drugs. base objects can extended additional information. Replicates Concentration user can one function: Additionally, user may fill full response data day 0 part. step, user may generate set synthetic results: Hill coefficient EC50 metric E inf metric user can create full response data one function (single-agent): SUMMARY
code: cell_lines <- create_synthetic_cell_lines() drugs <- create_synthetic_drugs() cl_rep <- add_data_replicates(cell_lines) head(cl_rep) cl_conc <- add_concentration(cell_lines) head(cl_conc) df_layout <- prepareData(cell_lines, drugs) head(df_layout) df_layout_small <- prepareData(cell_lines[seq_len(2), ], drugs[seq_len(4), ]) df_layout_small$Duration <- 72 df_layout_small$ReadoutValue <- 0 df_layout_small_with_Day0 <- add_day0_data(df_layout_small) head(df_layout_small_with_Day0) hill <- generate_hill_coef(cell_lines, drugs) ec50_met <- generate_ec50(cell_lines, drugs) einf_met <- generate_e_inf(cell_lines, drugs) response_data <- prepareMergedData(cell_lines, drugs) head(response_data)
